# Application Structure

This project uses Next.js with a hybrid of the App Router and Pages Router approaches.

## Main Components

- [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout component with global providers
- [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Main landing page
- [src/app/poster](mdc:src/app/poster) - Poster preview pages
- [src/app/docs](mdc:src/app/docs) - Documentation pages

## API Routes

API routes are implemented using the Pages Router in:

- [src/pages/api/generatePoster.ts](mdc:src/pages/api/generatePoster.ts) - Generate HTML poster
- [src/pages/api/generatePosterImage.ts](mdc:src/pages/api/generatePosterImage.ts) - Generate image from markdown
- [src/pages/api/getImage.js](mdc:src/pages/api/getImage.js) - Get stored images

## Markdown Processing

Markdown processing logic is located in the markdown directory:

- [src/markdown](mdc:src/markdown) - Markdown processing utilities

## Components

Reusable UI components are located in:

- [src/components](mdc:src/components) - UI components used throughout the application

